Next Steps:

  1. Run migrations to set up database tables:
     rails survey_engine:install:migrations
     rails db:migrate

  2. Mount the engine in config/routes.rb:
     mount SurveyEngine::Engine => "/surveys"

  3. Include the CSS in your application layout (app/views/layouts/application.html.erb):
     <%= stylesheet_link_tag "survey_engine", "data-turbo-track": "reload" %>

  4. Configure authentication in config/initializers/survey_engine.rb:
     - For Devise: config.current_user_email_method = lambda { current_user&.email }
     - For custom auth: modify as needed

  5. (Optional) Customize the CSS:
     - Edit app/assets/stylesheets/survey_engine.css
     - Modify CSS variables to match your design system

  6. (Optional) Generate custom controller for advanced customization:
     rails generate survey_engine:install --controller

Usage Example:

  # Create a survey template
  template = SurveyEngine::SurveyTemplate.create!(name: "Customer Satisfaction")
  
  # Add questions to template
  question = template.questions.create!(
    title: "How would you rate our service?",
    question_type: SurveyEngine::QuestionType.find_by(name: "scale"),
    order_position: 1,
    scale_min: 1,
    scale_max: 5
  )
  
  # Create a survey from template
  survey = SurveyEngine::Survey.create!(
    title: "Q1 2024 Satisfaction Survey",
    survey_template: template,
    surveyable: your_model # optional - attach to any model
  )

Available Question Types:
  - text: Short text input (single line)
  - textarea: Long text input (multi-line)
  - single_choice: Radio buttons
  - multiple_choice: Checkboxes
  - scale: Rating scale
  - boolean: Yes/No
  - number: Numeric input
  - matrix_scale: Matrix questions

Documentation: https://github.com/gonzalosanchez/survey_engine

